    "title": "Junior Android Engineer (m/f/d)",
    "description": "<p>Trade Republic is a European platform for mobile investing. With its intuitive app, people can save, invest, and trade on the capital markets commission-free with just three taps. Trade Republic's vision is for everyone to have the opportunity to take managing their investments into their own hands.</p>\n<p>Trade Republic is a bank licensed in Germany and supervised by the Bundesbank and BaFin. Their cooperation with well-known partners such as HSBC, BlackRock, and solarisBank underlines the high quality and security of their service. Trade Republic's investors include Accel, Creandum, Founders Fund, and Project A, as well as sino AG.</p>\n<p><strong>What you'll be doing</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Working with our existing Android team to help build and maintain new and existing features in the Trade Republic app</li>\n<li>Being involved in our feature processes, working closely with the product and design team to help refine our new features</li>\n<li>Work in a fast paced agile environment, where you will have the opportunity to take on responsibilities and ownership</li>\n<li>Work closely with experienced team members to deliver great value to our customers</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>About You</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>You are comfortable with Kotlin and the Android Framework</li>\n<li>You care about quality, and strive to achieve this both in code and for the product itself</li>\n<li>You have an eye for detail and a passion for UI/UX</li>\n<li>You enjoy working in an agile environment and have a self-driven personality with a “hands-on” approach</li>\n<li>You are a well rounded software developer who understands the importance of communication</li>\n<li>You are looking for an environment where you can have a large impact while continuing to develop and learn</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Tech Stack</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>100% Kotlin</li>\n<li>RxJava3</li>\n<li>MVVM</li>\n<li>Dependency Injection (Dagger2) and wide unit test coverage</li>\n<li>Retrofit/OkHttp</li>\n<li>WebSockets with a custom protocol, that bridges the reactive contract over the network</li>\n</ul>\n",
