    "company_url": "https://aws.amazon.com/de/",
    "location": "Berlin",
    "title": "Sr. Software Development Engineer - Amazon Redshift",
    "description": "<p>Are you passionate in building high quality products that users find super-efficient? Want to disrupt an industry by revolutionizing the way people view, manage and analyze huge volumes of data? Looking for a job where your work can have direct and massive impact on one of the newest and most exciting AWS services? If so, please read on about the opportunity to be a part of our team.</p>\n<p>We are looking for an expert software development engineer to join us to innovate on this new service that addresses the customer needs to set a new standard for data analytics tooling. If you have the skills for building high-performance and secure services that empowers services at massive scale, and are interested in cutting-edge cloud computing, this might be the job for you.</p>\n<p>Joining the Amazon Redshift team gives you the opportunity to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Work on the latest technology, as we constantly build the latest research concepts into our applications.</li>\n<li>Be part of something big, as you are working on a key pillar of AWSs extensive service portfolio and thousands of Amazon Redshift customers benefit from your contributions.</li>\n<li>Learn from the best, as you are working on challenging engineering tasks in a team of very experienced experts that are close to support you.</li>\n<li>Be part of a great team, as we invest a lot to create an inclusive environment that allows you to perform at your best, while maintaining a fun atmosphere.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>As a Senior Software Development Engineer at Amazon Redshift, you will:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Help define the system architecture, own and implement specific components, build highly available, secure, scalable, distributed and event-driven systems.</li>\n<li>Contribute to planning, architecture design, implementation, testing, and process improvement. Lead the design, implementation, and delivery of software in ambiguous and complex problem spaces.</li>\n<li>Participate in code and design reviews to maintain our high development standards</li>\n<li>As an early team member, you will take responsibility for technical problem solving, creatively meeting product objectives, and developing best practices</li>\n<li>Collaborate closely with UX designers, and other SDE team members to help define the scope of the product</li>\n<li>Find out what it takes to engineer secured systems for \"Amazon Scale\"</li>\n</ul>\n<p>BASIC QUALIFICATIONS</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, or a related technical discipline (or the equivalent)</li>\n<li>Extensive production experience with developing software services and an understanding of design for scalability, performance and reliability in a continuous-integration and continuous-deployment environment</li>\n<li>Proficiency in Node.js and experience with a variety of other modern programming languages (Java, JavaScript, C/C++)</li>\n<li>Proven problem-solving skills and knowledge of data structures, algorithms, object-oriented programming and systems design</li>\n<li>Production experience with relational or non-relational database systems</li>\n<li>Proven experience in designing, building, and operating large-scale distributed systems and web services on cloud providers</li>\n<li>Experience with the hiring and mentorship/leadership of junior engineers</li>\n</ul>\n<p>PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS</p>\n<ul>\n<li>7+ years of professional experience as an engineer working on highly scalable backend systems, preferably within AWS technologies</li>\n<li>3+ years of experience in Node.js development.</li>\n<li>A track record of successfully delivering projects as part of an agile software development team</li>\n<li>Excellence in technical communication with peers and non-technical cohorts</li>\n<li>Knowledge of professional software engineering practices and best practices for full software development life cycle, including coding standards, code reviews, source control management, continuous deployments, testing and operations</li>\n<li>Proven experience in being a self-starter who enjoys solving challenging problems and working in a fast-paced, flexible, and collaborative environment</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Explore all AWS Germany Senior Software Engineering roles available, meet our team members and get prepared for your interviews via link: <a href=\"https://awsseniorsoftwaregermany.splashthat.com/\">https://awsseniorsoftwaregermany.splashthat.com/</a></p>\n<p>Amazon is an equal opportunities employer. We believe passionately that employing a diverse workforce is central to our success. We make recruiting decisions based on your experience and skills. We value your passion to discover, invent, simplify and build.</p>\n<p>Protecting your privacy and the security of your data is a longstanding top priority for Amazon. Please consult our Privacy Notice to know more about how we collect, use and transfer the personal data of our candidates.</p>\n",
    "how_to_apply": "<p><a href=\"https://ad.doubleclick.net/ddm/clk/436616238;288615907;u?https://www.amazon.jobs/en/jobs/1122391/sr-software-development-engineer-amazon-redshift?cmpid=JBOTAW6348B&amp;utm_source=github.com&amp;utm_campaign=aws&amp;utm_medium=job_board&amp;utm_content=job_posting&amp;ss=paid\">https://ad.doubleclick.net/ddm/clk/436616238;288615907;u?https://www.amazon.jobs/en/jobs/1122391/sr-software-development-engineer-amazon-redshift?cmpid=JBOTAW6348B&amp;utm_source=github.com&amp;utm_campaign=aws&amp;utm_medium=job_board&amp;utm_content=job_posting&amp;ss=paid</a></p>\n",
